description:
QciTable:  A table storing configuration information for QoS Class Identifiers (QCIs) at specific cells within a radio access network, including timestamps, location, cell identifiers, and metadata.

dateTime: Timestamp of the QCI configuration record.
Area_Name: Name of the geographical area where the cell is located (e.g., NR cell in Balikpapan).
CellId: Unique identifier of the cell site.
Id2: Redundant cell identifier (appears to duplicate CellId).
Id3:  A placeholder or default identifier.
vsDataType: Type of data stored in the table (specific to Ericsson).
vsDataFormatVersion: Version of the Ericsson-specific data format.
QciTable.qciTableId:  Default identifier for the QCI table.
QciTable.reservedBy: Reserved field (currently empty).
